## Description

#### Implements
Implements the `addRoom` method of `CasinoInterface`.

#### Overrides
`N/A`

#### Purpose
Provides a way to add a new `PokerRoom` to the Casino‚Äôs list of managed rooms. This method is used to accommodate new gaming scenarios and player demand dynamically.

#### Events
- `casino:roomAdded`: This event is emitted after a room is successfully added. Listeners can use this to trigger updates or notifications.

#### Requirements
- The `room` parameter must be a valid instance of `PokerRoomInterface`.

---

## Casino - The class this method belongs to.

---

## Parameters
| Parameter Name | Type                | Default Value | Description                                |
|----------------|---------------------|---------------|--------------------------------------------|
| `room`         | `PokerRoomInterface`| `N/A`         | A `PokerRoom` instance to be added to the Casino.|

---

## Returns
| Type                  | Description                                |
|-----------------------|--------------------------------------------|
| `PokerRoomInterface[]`| The updated list of poker rooms in the Casino. |

---

## Throws
| Error Type    | Description                                |
|---------------|--------------------------------------------|
| `Error`       | If the `room` parameter is invalid.        |

---

## Usage
This method allows adding a new room to the Casino. After the room is added, an event is emitted to notify any subscribers.

---

## Examples
### Basic Example:
```typescript
const casino = new Casino();
const room = new PokerRoom({ name: "HighRollers", tableSize: 6, smallBlind: 10, bigBlind: 20 });
const updatedRooms = casino.addRoom(room);
console.log(updatedRooms); // Logs the updated list of rooms
